<paragraph id="8B87E76C6671FFC1FF0B057D6DC69ABD" blockId="23.[151,1437,621,1080]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FF0B057D696F9A99" bold="true" box="[151,305,621,648]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">Distribution.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6671FFC1FEA5057E6A7A9A99" author="Stevens, G. &amp; Fernando, D. &amp; Dando, M. &amp; Notarbartolo di Sciara, G." box="[313,548,622,648]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" refId="ref20333" refString="Stevens, G., Fernando, D., Dando, M. &amp; Notarbartolo di Sciara, G. (2018) Guide to the Manta and Devil Rays of the World. Princeton University Press, Princeton, New Jersey, 144 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / 9780691207216" type="book" year="2018">
Stevens 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FE04057F698F9A99" box="[408,465,622,648]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
list this species as likely occurring throughout the northern Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6671FFC1FAB5057E6D219A99" box="[1321,1407,622,648]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">Mexico</collectingRegion>
in offshore waters. Pelagic longline captures have occurred in waters ranging from nearly 1200 to over 
<quantity id="4CC04A896671FFC1FA9C05826D0B9ABD" box="[1280,1365,658,684]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" unit="m" value="2400.0">2400 m</quantity>
deep.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6671FFC1FF5B05A56CFD9AE5" blockId="23.[151,1437,621,1080]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FF5B05A569919AC1" bold="true" box="[199,463,693,720]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">First Record in GOM.</emphasis>
Verified captures in the pelagic longline fishery date back to 2008, but the first mention of the species occurrence in the northern GOM in the literature was by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6671FFC1FC2805CA6CC19AE5" author="Stevens, G. &amp; Fernando, D. &amp; Dando, M. &amp; Notarbartolo di Sciara, G." box="[948,1183,730,756]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" refId="ref20333" refString="Stevens, G., Fernando, D., Dando, M. &amp; Notarbartolo di Sciara, G. (2018) Guide to the Manta and Devil Rays of the World. Princeton University Press, Princeton, New Jersey, 144 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / 9780691207216" type="book" year="2018">
Stevens 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FB8E05CB6C159AE5" box="[1042,1099,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B4E76671FFC1FF5B05EE69059C29" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6671FFC1FF5B05EE6C0D9BDC" blockId="23.[151,1437,621,1080]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FF5B05EE69659B09" bold="true" box="[199,315,766,792]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">Remarks.</emphasis>
In their recent revision of the mobulid rays, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6671FFC1FCD705EE6C749B09" author="White, W. T. &amp; Corrigan, S. &amp; Yang, L. &amp; Henderson, A. C. &amp; Bazinet, A. L. &amp; Swofford, D. L. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P." box="[843,1066,766,792]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" pagination="50 - 75" refId="ref20831" refString="White, W. T., Corrigan, S., Yang, L., Henderson, A. C., Bazinet, A. L., Swofford, D. L. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P. (2018) Phylogeny of the manta and devilrays (Chondrichthyes: Mobulidae), with an updated taxonomic arrangement for the family. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 182 (1), 50 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zlx 018" type="journal article" year="2018">
White 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FC0605EF6B8B9B09" box="[922,981,766,792]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6671FFC1FB2B05EF6D1F9B09" baseAuthorityName="Müller &amp; Henle" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[1207,1345,767,792]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Mobula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FB2B05EF6D1F9B09" box="[1207,1345,767,792]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">M. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6671FFC1FAE205EF68A89B2D" authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1788" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Raia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mobular">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FAE205EF68A89B2D" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">M. mobular</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be conspecific, with precedence given to 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6671FFC1FD7C04336B3D9B2D" authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1788" box="[736,867,802,828]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Raia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mobular">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FD7C04336B3D9B2D" box="[736,867,802,828]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">M. mobular</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This effectively extended the range of 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6671FFC1FA8504336DC29B2D" authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1788" box="[1305,1436,802,828]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Raia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mobular">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FA8504336DC29B2D" box="[1305,1436,802,828]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">M. mobular</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
circumglobally in tropical to warm temperate waters. The taxonomic history of this species is long and convoluted but well reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6671FFC1FE10047A6A3C9B95" author="White, W. T. &amp; Corrigan, S. &amp; Yang, L. &amp; Henderson, A. C. &amp; Bazinet, A. L. &amp; Swofford, D. L. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P." box="[396,610,874,900]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" pagination="50 - 75" refId="ref20831" refString="White, W. T., Corrigan, S., Yang, L., Henderson, A. C., Bazinet, A. L., Swofford, D. L. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P. (2018) Phylogeny of the manta and devilrays (Chondrichthyes: Mobulidae), with an updated taxonomic arrangement for the family. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 182 (1), 50 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zlx 018" type="journal article" year="2018">
White 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FE44047B6A4E9B95" box="[472,528,874,900]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and Notarbartolo di Sciara 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FC07047B6B8A9B95" box="[923,980,874,900]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">et al.</emphasis>
(2020). The common name listed above reflects new insights discussed by Notarbartolo di Sciara 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FC8E049F6B149BB9" box="[786,842,910,936]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">et al.</emphasis>
(2020). This species is encountered as bycatch in the pelagic longline fishery in the northern GOM (
<figureCitation id="1303FBE96671FFC1FD3E04A26B4C9BDD" box="[674,786,946,972]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1979,2004]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1102,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,1102,1954]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mobula mobular captured by pelagic longline in the northern Gulf of Mexico. Photograph courtesy of NMFS SEFSC." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909141/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">Figure 14</figureCitation>
, C. Jones unpublished data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6671FFC1FF5B04C569059C29" blockId="23.[151,1437,621,1080]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FF5B04C5699F9BE1" bold="true" box="[199,449,981,1008]" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">Conservation Status.</emphasis>
Endangered, when assessed as 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6671FFC1FCBB04C76BF29BE1" authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1788" box="[807,940,982,1008]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Raia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mobular">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FCBB04C76BF29BE1" box="[807,940,982,1008]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">M. mobular</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in European waters, Near Threatened when assessed as 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6671FFC1FE8004EB69FA9C05" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1841" box="[284,420,1019,1044]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Cephaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="304" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="japanica">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6671FFC1FE8004EB69FA9C05" box="[284,420,1019,1044]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="304">M. japanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
globally. An updated assessment considering taxonomic changes and expansion of known range is required.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
